SERVER CREAATION --- NODE AND EXPRESS

BASIC COMMANDS
1.CREATING package.json ---npm init
2. INSTALL express---------npm i express
3. INSTALL JWT - npm i jsonwebtoken
4. INSTALL mongoose - npm i mongoose
5.  INSTALL cross  - npm i cors


BASIC STRUCTURE
1.CREATING A FOLDER
2.     "   package.json file
3.INSTALL express
4.create index.js file
5.import express inside index.js file
6.create app using express
7.setup port number
8.resolving http request
9.HTTP responce code
    1xx - information
    2xx - success
    3xx - redirection
    4xx - client error 
    5xx - server error
10.JWT(JSON WEB TOKEN) -AUTHENTICATION
  
                server generated token            request+number 
        Login -------------------------->client--------------------->server--->

        token generate - sign()

11.Middleware :
    1.Application specific middleware - for entire application - appMiddleware
    2.Router specific middleware - for token validation - jwtMiddleware
            verify() - token validation

12.Database Integration
        using mongoose
        db connection
        create model using mongoose

13.asynchronous function resolving
        resolve - .then()
        reject - catch()

14 CORS - cross origin resourse sharing(connect 2 different ports)
        install cors